    "As seen in the last row of Table 3, PoS provides approximately 7% better results than PoA and approximately 5% better results than PoW for sensitive data.",
    "PoW gives approximately the same results as PoA and approximately 8% better results than PoS for nonsensitive data.",
    "Figure 5 shows a graphical representation of Table 3.The processing power required for successful block creation in non-sensitive data is greater than that in sensitive data.",
    "It directly affects memory usage.",
    "Therefore, nonsensitive data require more memory usage."
